<subSubSection id="C31B6578E2662204E796F8400A2D900C" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBE36F3E2662204E796F8400A2D900C" blockId="0.[136,1452,1948,2076]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis id="B975EAE1E2662204E796F84008B89FA2" bold="true" box="[136,235,1948,1970]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="B975EAE1E2662204E7EFF841095A9FA2" bold="true" box="[241,265,1949,1970]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C014D70E2662204E617F84109EC9FA1" box="[265,447,1948,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ahooensis">
<emphasis id="B975EAE1E2662204E617F84109EC9FA1" box="[265,447,1948,1970]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Begonia ahooensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C014D70E2662204E524F8410A8B9FA1" authorityName="Dryander" authorityYear="1971" box="[570,728,1948,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis id="B975EAE1E2662204E524F8410A8B9FA1" box="[570,728,1948,1970]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Begonia grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the following characteristics: leaf margin entire, undulate (not irregularly serrulate); male-flowers with outer tepals sparsely pilose on reverse (not glabrous); female flowers with 5(3+2) tepals (not 3) and outer tepals pilose on reverse (not glabrous); stamens 11–44 (vs. 28–140); ovary hairy (not glabrous) with many distinct red dots and (not uniform pink or green) (
<tableCitation id="C6830348E2662204E536F7DA0A23900C" box="[552,624,2054,2076]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,157,183]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparative morphology of B. ahooensis and B. grandis subsp. grandis (Fl. China, Gu et al. 2007:176 and specimens in E)" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
